msgctxt "84_Kiryu"
msgid "How is he?"
msgstr "¿Cómo está?"

msgctxt "96_Haruka"
msgid "Not good. It looks like he's been having nightmares."
msgstr "No está bien. Ha estado teniendo pesadillas."

msgctxt "108_Kiryu"
msgid "Right... The doctor said he's exhausted. Probably malnourished, too."
msgstr "Right... The doctor said he's exhausted. Probably malnourished, too."

msgctxt "120_Haruka"
msgid "Hm..."
msgstr "Mm..."

msgctxt "132_Kiryu"
msgid "You're worried about him, aren't you? I can tell."
msgstr "You're worried about him, aren't you? I can tell."

msgctxt "144_Haruka"
msgid "Yeah. That, and..."
msgstr "Yeah. That, and..."

msgctxt "156_Kiryu"
msgid "You're still thinking about what he said on the beach."
msgstr "You're still thinking about what he said on the beach."

msgctxt "168_Haruka"
msgid "Uh-huh."
msgstr "Ajá."

msgctxt "180_Kiryu"
msgid "What about it?"
msgstr "What about it?"

msgctxt "192_Haruka"
msgid "That \"Hamazaki\" he mentioned... That's the guy who stabbed you last year."
msgstr "That \"Hamazaki\" he mentioned... That's the guy who stabbed you last year."

msgctxt "204_Haruka"
msgid "I'd never forget that name. And I can't trust someone who says they're friends with him."
msgstr "I'd never forget that name. And I can't trust someone who says they're friends with him."

msgctxt "216_Kiryu"
msgid "Believe me, I know how you feel."
msgstr "Believe me, I know how you feel."

msgctxt "228_Haruka"
msgid "If he's really friends with Hamazaki, I... I..."
msgstr "If he's really friends with Hamazaki, I... I..."

msgctxt "240_Kiryu"
msgid "Hate him?"
msgstr "Hate him?"

msgctxt "252_Haruka"
msgid "I... don't know."
msgstr "I... don't know."

msgctxt "264_Kiryu"
msgid "Listen, Haruka."
msgstr "Listen, Haruka."

msgctxt "276_Kiryu"
msgid "Even if he does know Hamazaki, that doesn't automatically mean he's a bad person."
msgstr "Even if he does know Hamazaki, that doesn't automatically mean he's a bad person."

msgctxt "288_Haruka"
msgid "But－"
msgstr "But－"

msgctxt "300_Kiryu"
msgid "Sure, Hamazaki was a bit unhinged the last time we met. But a lot can change in a year."
msgstr "Sure, Hamazaki was a bit unhinged the last time we met. But a lot can change in a year."

msgctxt "312_Kiryu"
msgid "When he lost the fight for the Tojo Clan, he lost the only thing that <Italic>meant</Italic> something to him. I was probably the only one he could take his anger out on."
msgstr "When he lost the fight for the Tojo Clan, he lost the only thing that <Italic>meant</Italic> something to him. I was probably the only one he could take his anger out on."

msgctxt "324_Haruka"
msgid "Maybe..."
msgstr "Tal vez..."

msgctxt "336_Kiryu"
msgid "If Hamazaki came to me now asking for help, I'd give it to him in a heartbeat."
msgstr "If Hamazaki came to me now asking for help, I'd give it to him in a heartbeat."

msgctxt "348_Kiryu"
msgid "As long as he's learned to have some faith in his fellow man, that is."
msgstr "As long as he's learned to have some faith in his fellow man, that is."

msgctxt "360_Haruka"
msgid "Uncle Kaz..."
msgstr "Uncle Kaz..."

msgctxt "384_Kiryu"
msgid "So, what do you say, Haruka?"
msgstr "So, what do you say, Haruka?"

msgctxt "396_Haruka"
msgid "Huh?"
msgstr "Uh, ¿y eso?"

msgctxt "408_Kiryu"
msgid "Do you really think he's a bad guy just because he knows Hamazaki?"
msgstr "Do you really think he's a bad guy just because he knows Hamazaki?"

msgctxt "420_Haruka"
msgid "I don't know <Italic>what</Italic> I think..."
msgstr "I don't know <Italic>what</Italic> I think..."

msgctxt "432_Kiryu"
msgid "He's a yakuza, no question. The tattoo's a dead giveaway."
msgstr "He's a yakuza, no question. The tattoo's a dead giveaway."

msgctxt "444_Kiryu"
msgid "But I have one of those too. He and I aren't so different in that respect."
msgstr "But I have one of those too. He and I aren't so different in that respect."

msgctxt "456_Haruka"
msgid "Yeah, but..."
msgstr "Sí, pero..."

msgctxt "468_Kiryu"
msgid "You've seen plenty of men like us over the years. Some good, some bad."
msgstr "You've seen plenty of men like us over the years. Some good, some bad."

msgctxt "480_Kiryu"
msgid "Where do you think he falls on that spectrum?"
msgstr "Where do you think he falls on that spectrum?"

msgctxt "492_Haruka"
msgid "Well, if I had to pick... I don't think he's a bad person."
msgstr "Well, if I had to pick... I don't think he's a bad person."

msgctxt "504_Kiryu"
msgid "Yeah?"
msgstr "¿Sí?"

msgctxt "516_Haruka"
msgid "But I can't say for sure. That's just the impression I get."
msgstr "But I can't say for sure. That's just the impression I get."

msgctxt "528_Kiryu"
msgid "All right, then. Good to know."
msgstr "All right, then. Good to know."

msgctxt "540_Haruka"
msgid "Huh? Are you going somewhere?"
msgstr "Huh? Are you going somewhere?"

msgctxt "552_Kiryu"
msgid "I have some shopping to do."
msgstr "I have some shopping to do."

msgctxt "564_Haruka"
msgid "Right now?"
msgstr "Right now?"

msgctxt "576_Kiryu"
msgid "Yeah. He'll need a nice meal when he comes to."
msgstr "Yeah. He'll need a nice meal when he comes to."

msgctxt "588_Kiryu"
msgid "The doctor said he hasn't been eating very well, after all."
msgstr "The doctor said he hasn't been eating very well, after all."

msgctxt "600_Haruka"
msgid "But aren't all the stores closed by now?"
msgstr "But aren't all the stores closed by now?"

msgctxt "612_Kiryu"
msgid "Don't worry, I'm sure somewhere in town will still be open."
msgstr "Don't worry, I'm sure somewhere in town will still be open."

msgctxt "624_Haruka"
msgid "Maybe, but..."
msgstr "Maybe, but..."

msgctxt "636_Kiryu"
msgid "What's wrong? Are you worried about being left alone with him?"
msgstr "What's wrong? Are you worried about being left alone with him?"

msgctxt "648_Haruka"
msgid "No, it's not that. It's just..."
msgstr "No, it's not that. It's just..."

msgctxt "660_Kiryu"
msgid "Relax. He's not going to hurt you. That's not the kind of man he is."
msgstr "Relax. He's not going to hurt you. That's not the kind of man he is."

msgctxt "672_Haruka"
msgid "...Okay."
msgstr "...Bien."

msgctxt "684_Kiryu"
msgid "Well, I should be going. I won't be gone long."
msgstr "Well, I should be going. I won't be gone long."

msgctxt "708_Haruka"
msgid "Please wake up, mister..."
msgstr "Please wake up, mister..."

msgctxt "720_Haruka"
msgid "Oh, he's opening his eyes!"
msgstr "Oh, he's opening his eyes!"

msgctxt "732_Saejima"
msgid "Urgh..."
msgstr "Urgh..."

msgctxt "744_Haruka"
msgid "I'm so glad you're okay!"
msgstr "I'm so glad you're okay!"

msgctxt "756_Saejima"
msgid "Huh? Where... am I?"
msgstr "Huh? Where... am I?"

msgctxt "768_Haruka"
msgid "This is Morning Glory Orphanage. We have lots of kids, but this is the first time we've taken in an adult."
msgstr "This is Morning Glory Orphanage. We have lots of kids, but this is the first time we've taken in an adult."

msgctxt "780_Saejima"
msgid "An orphanage?"
msgstr "An orphanage?"

msgctxt "792_Haruka"
msgid "Phew, I'm so glad you're okay, mister."
msgstr "Phew, I'm so glad you're okay, mister."

msgctxt "804_Haruka"
msgid "I was worried you were dead when I found you down on the beach..."
msgstr "I was worried you were dead when I found you down on the beach..."

msgctxt "816_Saejima"
msgid "Beach? What beach?"
msgstr "Beach? What beach?"

msgctxt "840_Saejima"
msgid "...Right. Must've washed up here."
msgstr "...Right. Must've washed up here."

msgctxt "852_Haruka"
msgid "Are you sure you're okay, mister?"
msgstr "Are you sure you're okay, mister?"

msgctxt "864_Saejima"
msgid "Think so."
msgstr "Think so."

msgctxt "876_Haruka"
msgid "My Uncle Kaz should be back any minute now."
msgstr "My Uncle Kaz should be back any minute now."

msgctxt "888_Haruka"
msgid "He thought you might've been shipwrecked, so he's checking in with the police. Don't worry, everything's gonna be okay."
msgstr "He thought you might've been shipwrecked, so he's checking in with the police. Don't worry, everything's gonna be okay."

msgctxt "900_Saejima"
msgid "The cops!?"
msgstr "The cops!?"

